Executive Profile
Charles H. Ogburn  Head of Global Corporate Investment, CSHM, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 8 Board Members in 8 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships61--
Background

		Mr. Charles H. Ogburn, also known as Charlie, served as Senior Managing Director of Suntrust Robinson Humphrey, Inc. Mr. Ogburn served as the Head of Corporate Investment at Arcapita Bank B.S.C.(c). He serves as the Head of Global Corporate Investment at CSHM, LLC. He served as the Head of Corporate Investment at Arcapita Bank B.S.C.(c), Investment Arm until 2010. Prior to joining Arcapita in 2001, he spent more than 15 years at The Robinson-Humphrey Company, Inc., as ... Senior Managing Director and Co-Head of Investment Banking. Prior to Robinson-Humphrey, he was an Attorney at King & Spalding for five years. He serves as the Non-Executive Chairman at The Crawford Group, Inc. He serves as the Chairman of Southland Log Homes, Inc. He has been the Non Executive Chairman of Crawford & Company since January 1, 2010 and its Director since February 3, 2009. He has been a Director of Tensar Corporation since September 2005 and Caribou Coffee Company, Inc. since January 2003. He has been a Trustee of Cook & Bynum Funds Trust - The Cook & Bynum Fund since May 2010. He serves as a Trustee at Georgia Research Alliance, Inc. and Children's Healthcare of Atlanta, Inc. He serves as a Director at the Atlanta Venture Forum and a Trustee of Trinity School. He served as an Executive Director of Arcapita Inc. and Arcapita Bank B.S.C.(c), Investment Arm. He served as a Director of Cypress Communications, Inc. He served as an Executive Director of Corporate Investment at AIM Group Limited. He served as a Director of American Pad & Paper LLC since September 2003. He serves as Vice Chairman of Children's Healthcare of Atlanta Foundation. He is a Member of the Society of International Business Fellows, a Member of the Rotary Club of Atlanta and a Member of the Advisory Board of Duke University Islamic Studies Center. Mr. Ogburn is a graduate of Duke University and earned a Degree in Law from Vanderbilt University School of Law.Read Full Background




